In .NET MAUI, lifecycle handling moved from `Application` to the **`Window`** class. Create a custom `Window` subclass and override its lifecycle methods:

```csharp
public class MyWindow : Window
{
    public MyWindow(Page page) : base(page) { }

    protected override void OnCreated()    { /* replaces OnStart */ }
    protected override void OnResumed()    { /* replaces OnResume */ }
    protected override void OnDeactivated(){ /* replaces OnSleep */ }
    protected override void OnDestroying() { /* new - app closing */ }
}
```

Then wire it up in your `App` class:

```csharp
public class App : Application
{
    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
        => new MyWindow(new MainPage());
}
```

**Key mappings:**
| Xamarin.Forms | .NET MAUI (`Window`) |
|---|---|
| `OnStart()` | `OnCreated()` |
| `OnSleep()` | `OnDeactivated()` |
| `OnResume()` | `OnResumed()` |

For **platform-specific** lifecycle events, you can also use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(a => a.OnStop(activity => { /* ... */ }));
#elif IOS
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios.DidEnterBackground(app => { /* ... */ }));
#endif
});
```
